## Limitations

This report is limited by the availability of recent empirical studies directly linking media violence censorship to societal outcomes. Additionally, the perspectives included are primarily from Western contexts, which may not fully represent global views on media censorship. Further research could explore longitudinal studies and cross-cultural analyses to provide a more comprehensive understanding of the issue.

